* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
* MMBT3904 (NPN) / MMBT3906 (PNP)  -  general-purpose BJTs, SOT-23
* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
* The MMBT390x are the SOT-23 packaging of the 2N390x die.  Per issue #10 the
* classic 2N3904/2N3906 Gummel-Poon models are accepted stand-ins (same die,
* different package).  These are the canonical onsemi/Motorola PSpice models,
* shipped verbatim in essentially every SPICE distribution.
*
* Source: onsemi "2N3903, 2N3904" and "2N3906" data sheets / PSpice model
*         libraries (Motorola process, model rev 1995-07).  Identical text is
*         mirrored in the ngspice, LTspice and KiCad standard model sets.
*
* Package note: MMBT390x adds a little lead/junction capacitance vs the TO-92
* 2N390x, negligible for the DC bias, output-impedance and audio-band AC work
* this deck performs.
* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

.model MMBT3904 NPN(IS=6.734f XTI=3 EG=1.11 VAF=74.03 BF=416.4 NE=1.259
+ ISE=6.734f IKF=66.78m XTB=1.5 BR=.7371 NC=2 ISC=0 IKR=0 RC=1
+ CJC=3.638p MJC=.3085 VJC=.75 FC=.5 CJE=4.493p MJE=.2593 VJE=.75
+ TR=239.5n TF=301.2p ITF=.4 VTF=4 XTF=2 RB=10)

.model MMBT3906 PNP(IS=1.41f XTI=3 EG=1.11 VAF=18.7 BF=180.7 NE=1.5
+ ISE=0 IKF=80m XTB=1.5 BR=4.977 NC=2 ISC=0 IKR=0 RC=2.5 CJC=9.728p
+ MJC=.5776 VJC=.75 FC=.5 CJE=8.063p MJE=.3677 VJE=.75 TR=33.42n
+ TF=179.3p ITF=.4 VTF=4 XTF=6 RB=10)
